    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.58"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">58</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">M. E. CONSTANTACATOS 
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="underline">17, SINA ST. &#8212; ATHENS</hi></hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 9, 1959.</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John Gneisenau Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Author</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim, <hi rend="capd">R.D.</hi> 6,</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Columbia, <hi rend="caps">MO.</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <list>
                    <item>(a) Money Supply and Price Stability</item>
                    <item>(b) Liquidity and the Price of Gold</item>
                </list>
                
                <milestone unit="section"/><ab>-------------------------------------</ab>
                
                <p>In my <hi rend="caps">REDEMPTION MESSAGE</hi>, herewith enclosed, I set forth in broad outline the Divine Law which governs both the supply of money and the price of gold.</p>
                
                <p>It is my hope that you will make time to read its contents with some attention, the more so as the rebellious children of the economic profession entertain the foolish belief that there exists no divine law governing our monetary affairs; and as a consequence they regard it unworthy of their scientific dignity to seek the face of the <hi rend="caps">LORD</hi>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours respectfully,</salute>
                
                    <signed>M C.</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note>Encl.</note>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>Kindly send me a copy of : 
                        <lb/>
                        "<hi rend="caps">THE SONG OF THE MESSIAH</hi>".</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
